.TH "sbi_remote_hfence_gvma" 9 "sbi_remote_hfence_gvma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sbi_remote_hfence_gvma \- Execute HFENCE.GVMA instructions on given remote harts for the specified guest physical address range.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sbi_remote_hfence_gvma
.BI "(const unsigned long *hart_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hart_mask" 12
A cpu mask containing all the target harts.
.IP "start" 12
Start of the guest physical address
.IP "size" 12
Total size of the guest physical address range.
.SH "RETURN"
None
